<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#43bca95c764a65a909b2dab7ef78ee3d>.
<#43bca95c764a65a909b2dab7ef78ee3d> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-03-10T06:15:18.795Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#43bca95c764a65a909b2dab7ef78ee3d> {
<https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Fysisk fostran och  träning"@sv, "Physical Education and Training"@en, "Randomiserad klinisk prövning [Publikationstyp]"@sv, "Randomized Controlled Trial"@en, "psykosocial stress"@sv, "physiological stress"@en, "HPA-axeln"@sv, "HPA-axis"@en, "akut stress"@sv, "acute stress"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__33941.
_:b0__33941 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/73c5795c7cd78b815120d3b824c01be2>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__86611.
_:b0__86611 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/d7e02f42f0642036b831ccc1d09c2a74>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2321000131>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Datamaterialet har använts i en studie som syftar till att undersöka effekterna av en träningsintervention på fysiologisk respons på akut stress. Totalt 88 individer ingår i materialet, samtliga har genomgått både baslinje- och uppföljande mätningar. Variablerna i materialet är bland annat ACTH, kortisol, syreupptag, puls och blodtryck."@sv, "The aim of the present trial was to study the effects of a six-month aerobic exercise intervention on the physiological response to acute laboratory stress. A two-armed RCT including untrained but healthy individuals aged 20-50 years was conducted. Assessments included a peak oxygen uptake test and a psychosocial stress test (the Trier Social Stress Test). A total of 88 participants went through both baseline and follow-up measures (48 in the intervention group and 40 in the control group) with an even distribution of women and men (20/28 in the intervention group and 18/22 in the control group, respectively). Outcome measures were adrenocorticotrophic hormone, cortisol, systolic- and diastolic blood pressure and heart rate responses to acute psychosocial stress.\n\nOutcome measures: adrenocorticotrophic hormone, cortisol, systolic- and diastolic blood pressure and heart rate responses to acute psychosocial stress."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2019-06-12T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.5878/p8e1-9s32>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2019-12-17T12:42:18Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
